<h2>Surly:</h2>
<p>
Surly is the most popular local brewer. Their popularity is well deserved. Hop lovers order Furious. Everyone else asks for Bender. Surly is widely available in Minneapolis (enter zip code 55402 <span class="content-link"><%= link_to "here", "http://www.surlybrewing.com/index.php?id=17", target: "_blank" %></span>) to find out where. Go get some.
</p>

<h2>Steel Toe:</h2>
<p>Steel Toe is just a couple of years old. Many think their Size 7 IPA is the best IPA made in Minnesota. It's not available at very many places, so get it if you see it. In downtown Minneapolis, Pizza Luce is the place most likely to have it. Protip: Go to the Steel Toe tap room. It's a 7 mile cab ride from the Westin. Check the <span class="content-link"><%= link_to "web site", "http://www.steeltoebrewing.com/ ", target: "_blank" %></span> for hours and directions.
</p>

<h2>Fulton Brewery:</h2>
<p>Another newcomer. Get Sweet Child of Vine if you're a hop lover. If you don't like hops, no worries, they make plenty of great beer. It's less than a mile walk from the Westin Hotel. You'll walk past Target Field. Go Twins! Check the Fulton <span class="content-link"><%= link_to "web site", "http://fultonbeer.com/the-brewery", target: "_blank" %></span> to make sure the tap room is open before you head over.
</p>

<h2>Summit:</h2>
<p>
Summit was the first craft brewery in Minnesota. They've grown so much that most people don't think of them as a craft brewer. Their beer is available just about everywhere. It's so easy to find that it's only recommended when your establishment doesn't have any of the other beers discussed here.
</p>

<h2>More:</h2>
<p>
Other local breweries with good reputations are 612, Brau Brothers, Indeed, Lift Bridge, Lucid. If you see it on tap, get some!
</p>
